Lab values: eGFR was calculated by Schartz2009 / eGFR calculated by CRCLSchwartz: 165,2 ml/min/qm. / GOT and GPT were done on 26.04.2022!                                 AUC/MPA+TAC were done on 08.03.2022 (day 48 after transplant): Tacrolimus on 08.03.2022: 8,9 µg/l, Mycophenolic acid on 08.03.2022: 1,43 mg/l                          Adverse Events Visit 6:                                                                                       Adverse Event 1: Adverse Event 1: Due to Hypertensive blood pressures during hospitalization after NTx persist, antihypertensive therapy with Amlodipin (Stop: 14.02.2022) and Clonidine (Stop:07.02.2022) was continued (see Adverse Event 1, Visit 5)!                                                                                                           Adverse Event 2: On 07.02.2022 there was a renewed Increase in creatinine (1.15 mg/dl) with febrile episodes despite the shock therapy with Methylprednisolone because of Banff IB rejection. A graft biopsy on 08.02.2022 revealed an Acute cellular rejection, Banff IIB (see Rejection!), so that a therapy with Antithymocite globulin was initiated and shock therapy was stopped (see Immunosuppression). In addition, because of Steroid-resistant rejection, Immunosuppressive therapy was changed back to Tacrolimus (Modigraf) on 07.02.2022 (see Change of Immunosuppressive Regimen)!                                                                   Adverse Event 3: Hyponatremia (120 mmol/l), which occurred on 07.02.2022, led to monitoring in the ICU until 09.02.2022!                                                       Adverse Event 4: Incidental findings showed Hypertriglyceridemia in the discharge blood sample after NTx stay (17.02.2022: 876 mg/dl), ongoing!                    Adverse Event 5: In case of recurrent Leucocyturia with detection of Escherichia coli and Klebsiella in urin culture from 28.02.2022, Urinary tract infection was diagnosed and oral antibiosis with Cefaclor started on 26.02.2022 was continued until 04.03.2022 (see Antibiotics)!                                                                    Adverse Event 6: In the evening of the day of admission for scheduled Tenckhoff catheter removal (09.03.2022), the patient developed subfebrile temperatures and the suspicion of Transplant pyelonephritis was confirmed. A calculated intravenous antibiosis with Ampicillin+Ceftazidime (08.03.2022-10.03.2022) was initiated, which was changed to an oral antibiosis with Cefaclor on 10.03.2022 (see Antibiotics!). The planned surgery was canceled (see Hospitalization 1)!                                        Adverse Event 7: Due to continued detection of Klebsiella pneumoniae in urine cultures, oral antibiotic treatment with Cefaclor was continued (stop: 31.03.2022) (see Antibiotics)!                                                                                               Adverse Event 8: Pronounced Left ventricular hypertrophy and a Tricuspid aortic valve were evident in an ECG during the inpatient stay for a rescheduled Tenckhoff catheter removal (23.02.2022) (see Hospitalization 2) -> Scheduled Cardio-MRT (see Visit 7)!                                                                                                         Visit 6: Anesthesia due to Transplant biopsy on 08.02.2022 was performed with Midazolam, Propofol and Alfentanil!                                                                       Aneshesia due to Tenckhoff catheter explantation on 23.03.2022 was performed with Sevofluran, Propofol, Antiemetics and Corticosteroids!                                      Visit 6 was performed 2 months and 3 weeks after transplant!

v270_general_comments: Faeces: Stool samples were collected at home on Visit Day (13.07.2022), but did not arrive at the clinic until 18.07.2022 -> 5 days old at the time of processing -> No change in Concomitant medication!                                                                      Urine: Sampling out of Permanent catheter!                                                          Lab values: eGFR was calculated by Schwartz2009 / eGFR calculated by CRCLSchwartz: 66,0 ml/min/qm.                                                                          AUC/MPA+TAC were not done!                                                                           Adverse Events Visit 7:                                                                                       Adverse Event 1: Recurrent pyelonephritis of the transplant kidney caused by Pseudomonas aeruginosa (see Hospitalization 1!). For this, empiric intravenous antibiotics with Meropenem+Teicoplanin in combination were started (20.04.2022-21.04.2022), which was continued with only Meropenem for 4 days after confirmed findings (22.04.2022-25.04.2022) (see Antibiotics!). In the case of increasing poor renal function, combined intravenous antibiotics with Ceftazidim+Ciprofloxacin were administered at a dosage adapted to renal function (26.04.2022-06.05.2022) (see Antibiotics!)! On the discharge day (Hospitalization 1), intravenous antibiotics with Ciprofloxacin were switched to oral intake (07.05.2022-22.05.2022). Furthermore, it was decided not to give another Pentacarinate inhalation (Stop: 12.04.2022), but instead to use Cotrimoxazole (Content of 60 mg TMP) as PCP prophylaxis again (Start: 07.05.2022) (see Antibiotics)!                                                               Adverse Event 2: Recurrent gastroenteritis with detection of Norovirus and Clostridium difficile in stool (see Hospitaization 1!). Therefore antibiotic therapy with Vancomycin (22.04.2022-13.05.2022) (see Antibiotics) and antimycotic therapy with Nystatin (22.04.2022-22.05.2022) (see Antimycotics) were given!                           Adverse Event 3: New onset hypertension on 13.07.2022 is treated intermittently with Amlodipin (see Co-Medication)!                                                                     Adverse Event 4: Due to a Recurrence of Severe Neutropenia on 19.05.2022 (Neutrophils absolute: 0.330/nl), PCP prophylaxis with Cotrimoxazole (Stop: 19.05.2022) was discontinued again and replaced by further Pentacarinate inhalations (Restart: 22.05.2022, ongoing) (see Antibiotics)! In addition, Immunosuppression with Mycophenolate Mofetil 500 mg/d was interrupted until further notice (Stop: 19.05.2022)!                                                                                                    Adverse Event 5: A renal function scintigraphy of the transplant kidney on 27.04.2022 showed the Persistence of the urodynamically relevant Urinary transport disorder °II, more prominent than in the previous examination (see Visit 6), which was not least the reason for the degradation of renal function (see Hospitalization 1)! Adverse Event 6: A positive PCR test on 01.06.2022 revealed a SARS Cov 2 infection with mild cough as symptomatic (01.06.2022-05.07.2022)! Therefore antibiotic therapy with Ciprofloxacin was restarted on 07.06.2022 and was also continued due to persistent Neutropenia (Neutrophils absolute on 13.07.2022: 1,22 /nl), ongoing (see Antibiotics)!                                                                                               Adverse Event 7: On 06.07.2022 first recognizable Glucosuria, progressive in the course!                                                                                                            Visit 7: In case of relevant stenosis of the Transplant anastomosis with Acute functional degeneration of the transplant kidney (creatinine increase from 0.8 mg/dl to 3.7 mg/dl), a Ureteral reimplantation was performed on 28.04.2022. Thereupon recovery of the kidney graft function. In the course of this surgery an intravenous anesthesia was performed with Midazolam, Ropivacain, Sevofluran, Propofol, Sufentanil, Remifentanil, Cisatracurium, Antiemetics, NSAR and Corticosteroids were given!                                                                                                              Visit was performed 6 months and one week after transplant!
